<Page x:Class="Hardcodet.Wpf.Samples.Help.Description"
	xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
	xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
	Title="Description" 
	>
    <FlowDocumentReader ViewingMode="Scroll">
        <FlowDocument FontSize="20">
            <Paragraph>
                <Image Source="/Images/help1.png" Width="190" Height="190" Margin="0,0,30,0" />
                <Run FontSize="30" BaselineAlignment="Center">Description</Run>

            </Paragraph>
            <Table CellSpacing="5" BorderThickness="1" BorderBrush="Black">
                <TableRowGroup>
                    <TableRow>
                        <TableCell>
                            <Paragraph>
                                <Image Source="/Images/Description.PNG"  Margin="5,5,5,5"  HorizontalAlignment="Center" />
                            </Paragraph>
                        </TableCell>
                    </TableRow>
                </TableRowGroup>
            </Table>

            <Paragraph>
                The Description Tab consists of three fields:
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        1. Title
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Title describes the script at high level so that other people will have a general ideal of what it does.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                2. Summary
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                 The Summary provides more details as to what the script does.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        3. Setup Instructions
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The setup instructions should provide details on what windows should be minimized, maximized, etc. before the script runs.  Also, if the focus should be set on a particular field before running the script, that should be noted as well.
            </Paragraph>


        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentReader>
</Page>
